name: thru 235 are reserved by ISO for the self-configurable address capability
notes: All devices in IG2 using preferred addresses shall be self-configurable.  IG2 devices shall include the value of the first full 32 bits of NAME field.  The self-configurable address capability is specified in ISO 11783-5

name: Data Logger
notes: A data logging server that provides the LOG functionality as specified in ISO 11783-10

name: TIM Server
notes: Control function that represents a Tractor Implement Management (TIM) Server.  TIM is an Operator Assistance System that enables TIM clients to request the control of certain TIM functions (for example speed, steering, hitch, PTO, hydraulic valves, etc.) from TIM servers.

name: Sequence Controller
notes: The master in the Sequence Control System as defined in ISO11783-14

name: Position Control
notes: Multiple axis position control of a devices movable device elements

name: Tractor ECU
notes: A gateway (see ISO 11783-4) between the tractor and the implement bus representing the tractor and its messages on the 11783 network

name: Tailings Monitoring
notes: Monitoring of the quantity of unthreshed material returned to threshing machine

name: Header Control
notes: Control of the headers reel rate and material delivery rate

name: Product Loss Monitoring
notes: Monitoring of the amount of produce being lost from e.g. a harvesting process

name: Product Moisture Sensing
notes: Monitoring of the produce moisture content

name: Non Virtual Terminal Display (Implement Bus)
notes: A non Virtual Terminal cab display connected to the implement bus

name: Task Control (Mapping Computer)
notes: A control function on the 11783 network that is responsible for the sending, receiving and logging of process data
